This paper deals with access control models for spatio-temporal data, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses confidentiality and security concerns, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of multiple space and time constraints and the need for optimization suggests that the paper may also be relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the scalability and handling of large amounts of data points to the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
